HEADWORD: Trellis
<hw>Trel"lis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>relis</ets>, F. <ets>treillis</ets>, fr. <ets>treille</ets> vine
arbor, fr. L. <ets>tricla</ets>, <ets>triclea</ets>, <ets>triclia</ets>,
a bower, arbor, summer house.]</ety> <def>A structure or frame of
crossbarred work, or latticework, used for various purposes, as for
screens or for supporting plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

